\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 1. A. thaliana} (L.) Heynh. in Holl & Heynh.,{\i  Fl. Sachs. }{\b 1}: 538 (1842) ({\i Sisymbrium thalianum }(L.) Gay). Annual or biennial up to 40(-70) cm, sparsely pubescent in the lower parts with mostly unbranched hairs on the stem and 2(3)-fid hairs on the leaves. Basal leaves entire to dentate; cauline usually entire, sessile, cuneate at the base. Petals 2-4(-4·5) mm, white; stamens 4-6; anthers 0·3-0·5 mm. Siliqua 5-20(-30) × 0·5-0·8 mm, glabrous, attenuate into style 0·3-0·5 mm. 2n = 10.{\i  Open habitats. Europe northwards to c.} 68°{\i  N.} All except Az Fa Is Sb.
\par

